Adding a comment works identically for issues and PRs because
GitHub's API treats them as the same comment endpoint. We use
[[gh issue comment]] which handles both:

<<helpers>>=
def gh_add_comment(repo, number, body):
    """Add a comment to a GitHub issue or PR.

    Works for both issues and pull requests since
    GitHub uses a shared comment endpoint.
    """
    result = subprocess.run(
        [
            "gh", "issue", "comment",
            str(number), "-R", repo,
            "--body", body,
        ],
        capture_output=True,
        text=True,
    )
    if result.returncode != 0:
        raise RuntimeError(
            f"gh comment failed: "
            f"{result.stderr.strip()}"
        )
@

\paragraph{Appending notes to items}
Several places need to add a note to a todo item---the [[note]]
command, headless output capture, and timeout handling.  Rather
than duplicating the GitHub-vs-local branching logic, we extract
a shared helper.  For GitHub-linked items we post a comment
\emph{and} store locally (belt-and-suspenders), because in
headless mode there is no human to notice a failed API call.

<<helpers>>=
def append_note_to_item(item, note_text, next_id, todos):
    """Append a note to a todo item.

    Posts to GitHub if linked, always stores locally.
    """
    if item.github:
        try:
            gh_add_comment(
                item.github["repo"],
                item.github["number"],
                note_text,
            )
        except Exception:
            logging.warning(
                "Failed to post GitHub comment "
                f"for #{item.id}"
            )
    if item.notes:
        item.notes += "\n" + note_text
    else:
        item.notes = note_text
    save_todos(next_id, todos)
@

\paragraph{Parsing timeout durations}
The [[--timeout]] option (see \cref{sec:headless-lifecycle})
accepts GNU [[timeout]]-style duration strings: a bare number
means seconds, or append [[s]], [[m]], [[h]], [[d]] for units.
The parser lives in [[track]] alongside other shared subprocess
helpers; we re-export it so that [[todo]]'s public API is unchanged.

