Most of the time we infer priority interactively by comparing the new
item with its siblings. Sometimes, however, the caller already knows the
numeric value or simply wants to add the item after the current lowest-
priority sibling. The [[--prio]] option handles the former case, while
[[--append]] keeps the latter non-interactive.

The new [[--skip-priority]] flag covers a third case: capturing a task
without ranking it yet.  That is useful when triaging a backlog or when
the right comparison set is not available at creation time.  Unranked
items sort after ranked ones until [[reprioritize]] assigns them a numeric
position:

<<argument and option definitions>>=
