Like the UNIX [[at]] command, we can capture the current working
directory and environment at creation time. The [[--here]] flag is a
convenient shorthand that captures both [[os.getcwd()]] and
[[os.environ]]. For finer control, [[--wd]] stores only an explicit
directory while [[--env]] stores only the current environment. This
lets the user update one without silently rewriting the other. The
[[--command]] option sets a default command (such as [[claude]] or
[[opencode]]) to launch when starting the todo.  The same attributes can
also be supplied per worker in the config via
[[todo.worker.<worker>.wd]], [[todo.worker.<worker>.env]], and
[[todo.worker.<worker>.command]].

