CSV output is intended for pipelines and scripts. We write
tab-separated values so that titles containing commas remain
unambiguous. A [[parent_id]] column preserves hierarchy
information that the tree view shows visually. Using
[[csv.writer]] handles quoting of any fields that happen to
contain tabs or newlines.

When writing to a file (via [[--output]]) we always include the
header row so the file is self-describing. When writing to a
terminal the header is shown for readability. When piping to
another process the header is omitted so that tools like [[awk]]
and [[cut]] receive only data rows.
Like the table and JSON paths, the priority field is omitted
by default and included when [[--prio]] is passed.

<<output csv>>=
if not filtered:
    return

now = datetime.datetime.now()
sorted_items = sort_todos_for_display(
    filtered, now
)[:count]
dest = open(output, "w", newline="") if output else sys.stdout
writer = csv.writer(dest, delimiter="\t")
if output or sys.stdout.isatty():
    writer.writerow([
        "id",
        *( ["priority"] if show_prio else [] ),
        "title", "who",
        "deadline", "estimated_h", "tracked_h",
        "status", "parent_id",
    ])
for item in sorted_items:
    ep = effective_priority(item, now)
    tracked = tracked_times.get(item.id, 0)
    writer.writerow([
        item.id,
        *([
            "" if ep is None else f"{ep:.1f}"
        ] if show_prio else []),
        item.title,
        item.who or "",
        item.deadline or "",
        (
            f"{item.estimated:.1f}"
            if item.estimated
            else ""
        ),
        f"{tracked:.1f}" if tracked > 0 else "",
        item.status,
        item.parent_id if item.parent_id else "",
    ])
if output:
    dest.close()
    typer.echo(f"Wrote todos to {output}")
@

\subsection{The [[view]] Command}

The [[view]] command displays a single todo with all its details and
children in a readable format. This is the read-only counterpart to
the editor---you can see exactly what [[--edit]] would show, without
opening an editor.

When no ID is given, [[view]] shows the current active task---the one
you're currently working on.  In tmux that means the current pane or
window context.  If tmux is active but this pane/window is untracked,
there is no implicit active todo and the user must supply an ID.
Outside tmux it falls back to the worker's active-stack top.  This is
the natural question a returning user asks:
\enquote{What was I doing?}

Because [[note]] and [[done]] follow the same convention, [[view]] now
uses the shared [[resolve_todo_id()]] helper rather than reimplementing
 the stack lookup inline.

<<argument and option definitions>>=
todo_id_arg = typer.Argument(
    help="Todo ID (default: current active todo)",
    autocompletion=complete_todo_ids)
@

<<view command>>=
@cli.command()
def view(
    todo_id: Annotated[int | None,
                       todo_id_arg] = None,
    include_done: Annotated[bool,
                            done_opt] = False,
):
    """View a todo item with full details.

    If no ID given, shows the current active task.
    Done sub-items are
    hidden by default; pass --done to include them.
    """
    _, todos = load_todos()

    todo_id = resolve_todo_id(
        todo_id, "view",
        who=default_username, todos=todos,
    )

    item = next(
        (t for t in todos if t.id == todo_id), None
    )
    if item is None:
        typer.echo(
            f"Error: todo #{todo_id} not found",
            err=True,
        )
        raise typer.Exit(1)

    <<display todo details>>
    <<display todo children>>
@

<<display todo details>>=
typer.echo(
    f"#{item.id} {item.title} [{item.status}]"
)
parts = []
if item.priority is not None:
    parts.append(f"Priority: {item.priority:.1f}")
else:
    parts.append("Priority: unset")
if item.deadline:
    parts.append(f"Deadline: {item.deadline}")
if item.estimated:
    parts.append(f"Est: {item.estimated:.1f}h")
if parts:
    typer.echo("  " + "  ".join(parts))
meta_parts = []
if item.labels:
    meta_parts.append(
        f"Labels: {', '.join(item.labels)}"
    )
if item.who:
    meta_parts.append(f"Worker: {item.who}")
if meta_parts:
    typer.echo("  " + "  ".join(meta_parts))
if item.wd:
    typer.echo(f"  WD: {item.wd}")
if item.command:
    typer.echo(f"  Command: {item.command}")
if item.github:
    gh = item.github
    typer.echo(
        f"  GitHub: {gh['repo']}"
        f"#{gh['number']} ({gh.get('type', 'issue')})"
    )
if item.description:
