\subsection{Testing the [[--parent]] Flag}

Reparenting addresses the common accident of creating a todo as a
child of an active item when a top-level item was intended.  We
verify both directions: promoting a child to the top level and
moving it under a different parent.  We also confirm that supplying
an invalid parent ID is rejected with a non-zero exit code rather
than silently storing a dangling reference.

