That delegation removes the need for a separate stale-label sweep here.
If a todo wrapper decides that [[todo:N]] should stop, it should ask the
track module to stop it explicitly and immediately.  Keeping a hidden
cleanup pass in [[cli.todo]] would blur the boundary between todo state
and tracking state again.

When a todo linked to a GitHub issue or PR is marked done, we also
close the corresponding item on GitHub. This keeps the two systems
in sync without requiring a separate [[sync]] step. We catch
errors gracefully---network issues should not prevent the local
state change from completing.

