Restarting an already-active task (e.g.\ after a failed run) must
not push a duplicate onto the stack, otherwise [[todo done]] would
only remove one copy and leave a stale entry.
[[activate_todo_state]] checks membership before appending.

Let's verify that starting a task pushes it onto the stack:

