\subsection{The [[note]] Command}

The [[note]] command adds a note to a todo item. For
GitHub-linked items, it posts a comment on the issue or PR. For
local items, it appends to the [[notes]] field.

Like [[view]] and [[done]], [[note]] defaults to the currently active
todo when no ID is given.  This keeps the common workflow short:
start work, then record progress without retyping the task number.

Message source follows a priority chain: [[--message]] flag
first, [[--edit]] opens an editor, and if neither is given, we
read from standard input. This mirrors [[git commit]]'s
[[--message]] vs editor workflow.

<<argument and option definitions>>=
note_message_opt = typer.Option(
    "--message", "-m",
    help="Note text (inline)")
@

<<note command>>=
@cli.command()
def note(
    todo_id: Annotated[int | None,
                       todo_id_arg] = None,
    message: Annotated[str | None,
                       note_message_opt] = None,
    edit: Annotated[bool, editor_opt] = False,
):
    """Add a note to a todo item."""
    next_id, todos = load_todos()
    todo_id = resolve_todo_id(
        todo_id, "add a note",
        who=default_username, todos=todos,
    )
    item = next(
        (t for t in todos if t.id == todo_id), None
    )
    if item is None:
        typer.echo(
            f"Error: todo #{todo_id} not found",
            err=True,
        )
        raise typer.Exit(1)

    <<resolve note text>>
    <<post or append note>>
@

<<resolve note text>>=
if message:
    note_text = message
elif edit:
    initial = ""
    if not item.github and item.notes:
        initial = item.notes
    note_text = open_editor(initial)
    if not note_text.strip():
        typer.echo("Empty note, cancelled.")
        raise typer.Exit(0)
else:
    note_text = sys.stdin.read()
    if not note_text.strip():
        typer.echo("Empty note, cancelled.")
        raise typer.Exit(0)
@

<<post or append note>>=
if item.github:
    require_gh()
append_note_to_item(item, note_text, next_id, todos)
if item.github:
    gh = item.github
    typer.echo(
        f"Comment posted on "
        f"{gh['repo']}#{gh['number']}"
    )
else:
    typer.echo(f"Note added to #{todo_id}")
@

The [[note]] command routes through two paths: GitHub comments for
linked items, or local append for unlinked items. Let's verify
both:

